<p>So Im trying to get this to work, but so far Ive had no luck and could use some help. I have an app made in unity and a receiver plugin I made to handle the broadcast of the referrer.  Here is the receiver plugin handler so far just to test execution. </p>  <p>AnalyticsHandler.java</p>  <pre><code>import android.content.BroadcastReceiver; import android.content.Context; import android.content.Intent; import android.util.Log;  public class AnalyticsHandler extends BroadcastReceiver {     @Override     public void onReceive(Context context, Intent intent) {         Log.d("AnalyticsHandler", "-------------------onRecieve Hit---------------");     } } </code></pre>  <p>Im using this in the AndroidManifest snippet of the referrer part in unity and plugin</p>  <p>AndroidManifest.xml</p>  <pre><code>&lt;service android:name="com.google.android.gms.analytics.CampaignTrackingService" /&gt; &lt;receiver android:name="com.my.plugin.AnalyticsHandler"           android:exported="true"&gt;   &lt;intent-filter&gt;     &lt;action android:name="com.android.vending.INSTALL_REFERRER" /&gt;   &lt;/intent-filter&gt; &lt;/receiver&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Lastly Im testing it with the following command in adb</p>  <pre><code>./adb shell broadcast -a com.android.vending.INSTALL_REFERRER -n "com.my.plugin/com.my.plugin.AnalyticsHandler" --es referrer "utm_source=testSource&amp;utm_medium=testMedium&amp;utm_term=testTerm&amp;utm_content=testContent&amp;utm_campaign=testCampaign" </code></pre>